# v16 retakes (STD, 480p): python3 ../pool_run.py videos_v16.sh outputs/video16 3
# a_smoke: Deshawn must be STANDING (he was back in the chair in the first insert)
# q2: bad dub + too much back-thumping -> native retake, minimal contact
# q3: Deshawn/Milo off-model (no anchors last time) + Cass walked backwards

NEG="Photorealistic, natural human motion and facial performance, correct anatomy and proportions. No slow motion unless stated. No text, captions or subtitles appearing anywhere. Characters keep exactly the same faces and clothes as in the reference images for the entire clip. Each character appears exactly once. Voices match the provided audio reference."
WARC="Wardrobe and character lock: Cass is 17, white, lean, pale, short dark tousled hair, watchful grey eyes, wearing a plain heather-grey t-shirt, dark slim jeans, white sneakers. Milo is 17, white, compact, curly brown hair, thin wire-frame glasses, wearing an olive-green hoodie and blue jeans. Deshawn is 17, Black, very tall and long-limbed, buzzed hair, iridescent blue-and-orange track jacket. The arcade is spotless and gleaming, magenta and cyan neon."

gen a_smoke_stand 5 "Deshawn STANDING beside the white pod chair in the neon arcade, exactly as in the start image - he remains standing on his feet for the entire clip, never sitting. He leans down toward the chair, delighted, and calls out teasingly, his voice matching the audio reference: 'Ohhh - Cass wants the SMOKE!' Then he straightens up and cackles, thrilled. Magenta and cyan neon, arcade cabinets glowing behind him. $WARC $NEG" --start-image $F2/f_deshawn_standing.png --image $A/deshawn.png --audio $A/voice/deshawn.m4a

gen q2_longtime2 8 "Cass sits in the white pod chair, headset already off and staying off, staring at his own hands. Milo leans in over the chair, grinning: 'What did you DO in there? Nobody plays maxed out!' Cass looks up from his hands and says, quiet and completely level, his voice matching the audio reference: 'I lived a long time.' A beat - then Deshawn and Milo crack up laughing at the absurdity; Deshawn claps him on the shoulder exactly ONCE, briefly. Cass does not laugh at all, still looking at his hands. Nobody touches him after the single shoulder clap. $WARC $NEG" --start-image $F/8_1_headset_off.png --image $A/cass_17.png --image $A/milo.png --image $A/deshawn.png --audio $A/voice/cass_teen.m4a

gen q3_walk2 6 "Night. Clean bright suburban street under humming smart streetlights. Deshawn and Milo goof around ahead, re-enacting a ski crouch, laughing - their faces exactly matching the reference images. Cass trails a few steps behind them, walking FORWARD in the same direction they walk, hands in pockets, and slows, looking around at the street - too clean, too easy - like a man reading a room. Distant, Deshawn calls back: 'Bro's still IN there!' $WARC $NEG" --start-image $F/8_2_night_walk.png --image $A/cass_17.png --image $A/deshawn.png --image $A/milo.png --audio $A/voice/deshawn.m4a
